15,000 small scale farmers will each receive R50,000 from the COVID-19 relief fund. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - Up to 15,000 small scale farmers will each receive R50,000 from the COVID-19 relief fund. Agriculture Minister Thoko Didiza says the intervention of R1.2-billion is an attempt to offset the negative impact of the coronavirus and ensure sustainable food production after the pandemic. WATCH: Coronavirus in the Cape Winelands Didiza was speaking at a briefing in Pretoria. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.